  "prompt": "Why did the Philippine president Rodrigo Duterte call Barack Obama a \"son of a bitch\"?",
  "response": "Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte called then-U.S. President Barack Obama a \"son of a bitch\" in September 2016. The remark was made during a press conference before Duterte's trip to Laos for an ASEAN summit. Duterte's outburst was in response to potential criticism from Obama regarding Duterte's controversial and violent campaign against illegal drug use in the Philippines, which had drawn widespread international condemnation due to extrajudicial killings.\n\nDuterte's use of such derogatory language prompted a swift reaction, and Obama subsequently canceled a planned meeting with Duterte. Duterte's comments were seen as a significant diplomatic incident and highlighted the tension and strained relations between the United States and the Philippines at that time.",
